--- User Connection: VLESS+TCP (no TLS) ---
{{ vless_relay_url }}

--- Chain Path ---
User → {{ ansible_host }}:{{ relay_inbound_port | default(443) }} (relay, VLESS+TCP)
     → {{ exit_ip }}:443 (exit, VLESS+Reality+XHTTP)
     → Internet

--- Routing ---
Russian sites (geosite:ru, geoip:ru) → DIRECT from relay
Everything else → exit node → Internet

--- Recommended Client Apps ---
iOS:      v2RayTun (App Store) or Hiddify
Android:  v2rayNG (Play Store) or Hiddify
Windows:  v2rayN (github.com/2dust/v2rayN/releases)
macOS:    Hiddify (github.com/hiddify/hiddify-app/releases)

--- Important Notes ---
1. WHITELISTED IP: This relay must be on a whitelisted Russian IP.
   Test by deploying a web server and accessing from mobile (MTS/Megafon).

2. DOMESTIC TRAFFIC: No TLS/Reality on the user→relay leg. This is
   intentional — domestic traffic is not scrutinized by TSPU.

3. RUSSIAN SITES: Traffic to Russian domains goes directly from the relay
   without routing through the exit node (lower latency).

4. TIME SYNC: Device clock must be accurate within 30 seconds.

5. IF EXIT NODE CHANGES: Re-run playbook-chain.yml to update the relay's
   outbound configuration with the new exit node credentials.

